<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.2. "><span style="color: rgb(255,0,0);">#Fix</span> Overview</h2>
<p>
    This page documents the parts of the Product Search, Bulk Upload and Product/CPN validation flow that are
    identical across intake types: the MM/CPN search UI mechanics, the PO History &amp; Validate PO button flow, the
    Bulk Upload CSV mechanics, and the CPN Indicator Check.
</p>
<p>
    <strong>Purpose:</strong> Give Developers and QA a single reference for the search/upload/validation UI
    mechanics that are genuinely shared across intake types, so they are documented once.
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002" ac:name="warning" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Important: this page is deliberately thin</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Unlike Address/Contact Management, most of "Product Validation" is <strong>not</strong> identical across
            intake types. The PO History validation API name, the initial date range/lookback window, the allowed
            Item Type value(s), bulk-upload line caps, Return Package Condition values, and the Disti Channel Product
            Status code lists all genuinely differ by intake page (and in Technical's case, the PO History date
            logic is a structurally different warranty-driven algorithm, not just a different constant). Do not move
            those details here; they stay on each intake page. This page only covers the mechanics that are
            actually the same everywhere.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Reusable page: link here, do not copy</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            Link to this page for the mechanics below instead of repeating them. Each intake page keeps its own
            API name, date range, Item Type value(s), line caps, Return Package Condition values, and Product
            Status code list inline, since those genuinely differ by Service Type.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.3. ">MM/CPN Product Search: UI Mechanics</h2>
<ul>
    <li>When the agent selects the Product Search option, they are presented with two options and select one.</li>
    <li>Agent can search with one or more MM or CPN by selecting the respective radio button.</li>
    <li>After the agent selects one option and enters the related data, they get the related line-item data by
        clicking the "Search" button.</li>
    <li>If the agent searches using <strong>MM</strong>, the data entered is validated in the SF database, and
        valid MM numbers are then sent to the MM-CPN API to get the respective CPN numbers for the MMs.</li>
    <li>If the agent searches using <strong>CPN</strong>, data is sent first to the MM-CPN API to get the required
        MMs, and all valid MMs obtained are re-validated in the database to get product details.</li>
    <li>The line-item data obtained is further validated by Item Type. <em>See the intake page for the allowed
        Item Type value(s), which differ by Service Type.</em></li>
    <li>Valid line items are displayed in the table with related product information from the database.</li>
    <li>Line items that fail validation are shown disabled, with the validation error shown on the 'i' icon in the
        validation column.</li>
    <li>If all entered data fails validation, it is a hard stop and the agent is notified via error toast.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: Multiple CPN Scenario</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <ul>
            <li>For some MMs, there's a chance of getting multiple CPN numbers for a single MM from the MM-CPN API.</li>
            <li>In this scenario, the agent is shown a popup of the MM and its corresponding CPNs. The agent can
                select any CPN from the dropdown and submit; the selected CPNs are then populated and used for the
                respective line items.</li>
        </ul>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.4. ">PO History &amp; Validate PO: Button Flow</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Agent can select the required line items and click the 'PO History' button to get the required PO data for
        the selected line items. <em>See the intake page for which API this calls and the initial date range/
        lookback window, since these differ by Service Type.</em></li>
    <li>If PO numbers are found for all required line items, the agent can proceed directly.</li>
    <li>If PO numbers are not found for all selected line items, an error is shown (wording varies by page).</li>
    <li>Agent can also enter PO numbers manually in the input box for each valid line item; the entered PO number is
        validated from the API.</li>
    <li>The 'Validate PO' Number line is bypassed at the PO History step; if a line failed at the Validate PO step,
        that line item is a hard stop (Hardstop).</li>
    <li>Until PO validation is done, the agent cannot proceed further. If all entered data fails validation, it is a
        hard stop and the agent is notified via error toast.</li>
    <li>Once the PO History check is done, the agent can proceed to the next step by clicking 'Next'.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.5. ">Bulk Upload: CSV Mechanics</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Along with search functionality, the agent can also upload line-item data using the 'Bulk Upload'
        functionality.</li>
    <li>Agent is provided the option to download the CSV template and enter the required line-item data.</li>
    <li>Agent can upload the file either by clicking the upload button and selecting the file, or by dragging and
        dropping the CSV file onto the 'drop files' area.</li>
    <li>Mandatory fields per line item, line caps, and the allowed Return Package Condition / Box Condition values
        differ by intake page. <em>See the intake page for those.</em></li>
    <li>Once the agent uploads the CSV file, they click the 'Validate' button for the line-item data to be read and
        validated.</li>
    <li>If an empty file, or a file with a format other than '.csv', is uploaded, the agent is notified with an
        error toast.</li>
    <li>If the file is missing any required field for any line item, the agent is notified with an error toast and
        an Error Description Screen shown under the upload UI, listing the line numbers with errors; the file can be
        downloaded as <code>Bulk_Upload_Results.csv</code> with the error message in an additional column.</li>
    <li>If the uploaded data contains only MM numbers, the MM-CPN API is used to get the respective CPN numbers; if
        only CPN numbers, the MM-CPN API is used to get the respective MM numbers; if a combination, both are
        resolved.</li>
    <li>After upload and validation, if an MM number is auto-replaced with another MM number, the agent is shown a
        pop-up explaining the replacement.</li>
    <li>The resulting line items are then validated by Item Type (see the intake page for allowed value(s)), and
        valid line items are displayed with related product data.</li>
    <li>Agent proceeds to PO History / Validate PO the same way as the search path above.</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.6. ">Disti Channel Product Status Check</h2>
<p>
    After the PO History step, a Disti Channel Product Status check runs against an allowed/not-allowed code list.
    If the product status is not on the allowed list, it is a hard stop and the agent is shown an error message
    naming the current status. If the product status is missing or invalid, the agent sees "No valid product status
    were found".
</p>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">This check reads a different field depending on the IAO flag</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            When the IAO flag is on, the check reads the numeric field
            <code>Sales_Issue_Channel_StatusCode_Numeric__c</code> against the
            <code>Agent_Allowed_Product_Status_IAO</code> / <code>Portal_Allowed_Product_Status_IAO</code> custom
            labels. When the flag is off (non-IAO), it instead reads the letter-coded field
            <code>Sales_Issue_Disti_Channel_prd_Status_Cd__c</code> against the
            <code>Agent_Allowed_Product_Status</code> / <code>Portal_Allowed_Product_Status</code> labels. This is
            why some intake pages document numeric status codes (e.g. 35, 45, 75) and others document letter codes
            (e.g. AC, RS, EN); they are not contradicting each other, they are each documenting one flag state.
            Every intake page should state <strong>which flag state its documented code list applies to</strong>,
            and list the actual allowed/not-allowed codes for that state on the intake page itself (not here),
            since the label values can also differ by Service Type.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.7. ">CPN Indicator Check</h2>
<ul>
    <li>When the user clicks 'Save &amp; View Summary' or 'Save for Later', an additional validation called 'CPN
        Indicator check' is done. For the selected Sold To CMF, the value of the 'Is CPN required?' field is
        fetched.</li>
    <li>If the field value is 'True', all line items are validated for CPN values.</li>
    <li>Any line item that doesn't have a CPN value is disabled and shown to the agent, with the corresponding error
        message in the validation column.</li>
</ul>
<ac:structured-macro ac:macro-id="20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006" ac:name="info" ac:schema-version="1">
    <ac:parameter ac:name="title">Note: CPN Support Customer (applicability varies by page)</ac:parameter>
    <ac:rich-text-body>
        <p>
            On some intake pages, for a "CPN Support Customer," if CPN is not available for a line item, the MM-CPN
            API is called on click of 'Save for Later' / 'Save &amp; View Summary' to populate the CPN at line-item
            level; otherwise the line items without a CPN are disabled with an error message. Confirm on the intake
            page whether this note applies before assuming it does; it was not found on every page.
        </p>
    </ac:rich-text-body>
</ac:structured-macro>
<h2 data-nh-numbering="1.8. ">Where this is used</h2>
<p>
    Link to this page from the Product Search / Bulk Upload / CPN Indicator Check sections of intake pages instead
    of duplicating the shared mechanics. Pages that link here: Admin Intake, Exception Intake, Quality Intake, Stock
    Rotation Intake, Technical Intake, Miscellaneous Intake. Miscellaneous Intake did not have a CPN Indicator
    Check section at all at the time this page was created; that gap was not filled in here and should be checked
    with whoever owns that page rather than assumed.
</p>
